                            <comment id="12881554" author="peterg" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2010 06:34:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch adds a job.setJarByClass(KMeansDriver.class) line to the KMeansDriver.java code, ensuring that the job classpath is set up correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885534" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 14:22:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It works for me w/o the modification.  What steps did you do to reproduce this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing it works for me b/c I did a mvn install first.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At any rate, the patch seems fine, too, just curious why I&apos;m not seeing it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885544" author="drew.farris" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 14:57:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;IIRC, this doesn&apos;t show up when running locally but does come up when running on a hadoop cluster. Can&apos;t verify at the moment however.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885578" author="peterg" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 17:14:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran into this issue when deploying on a Hadoop install on an EC2 machine, following the EC2 deployment instructions on the wiki.  I ran through the steps (starting from a clean server) multiple times, and I reproduced this issue each time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885595" author="tdunning" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 17:48:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;THis looks non-controversial and safe.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885603" author="tdunning" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 18:05:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied Peter&apos;s patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885609" author="hudson" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 18:22:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #120 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/120/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/120/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-428&quot; title=&quot;KMeansDriver: No job jar file set leads to ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.mahout.clustering.kmeans.KMeansMapper&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-428&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-428&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Applied Peter&apos;s patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13098312" author="danbri" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 21:10:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Related: this seems to be a problem with spectral clustering too, informally reported at &lt;a href=&quot;http://spectrallyclustered.wordpress.com/2010/07/14/sprint-3-quick-update/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://spectrallyclustered.wordpress.com/2010/07/14/sprint-3-quick-update/&lt;/a&gt; ( I&apos;m chatting with Shannon now). If I confirm it on a clean install I&apos;ll raise a fresh jira, ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
